The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, June 28, 2004 				 LG charts growth plans with Care
 A STAFF REPORTER				 	 Aiming high																								Calcutta, June 27: LG is eyeing the second slot in the FMCG (fast moving consumer goods) market and has set a turnover target of Rs 500 crore in the next three years.																								Speaking at the launch of the LG Care brand, Managing director Vijay R. Singh said, The launch was preceded by 18 months of market research and setting up a strong distribution network. We have revised our projections from Rs 100 crore to Rs 150 crore for the first year of operations based on the pre-launch response.																								The company has launched seven categories of products, including soaps, shampoo, toothpaste and detergents, under the LG Care brand. The LG group subsidiary plans to launch all the 20 categories available in the international market in a phased manner.																								The promotional budget for the first year has been set at Rs 30 crore with Rs 12 crore as capital expenditure, said Singh. The products will be sold in 14 states through 500 distribution networks and 300,000 retail outlets.																								Singh said the company expects 17 to 20 per cent of the overall sales from the eastern region. 																								This is the first time that an umbrella branding strategy is being followed in the FMCG segment, added Singh. Our products have been re-designed into smaller packs to meet market demands and also developed to suit Indian conditions.																								Singh said the company would consider local sourcing of products once a critical mass is reached.																								We will then consider alliances with local manufacturers, he said. Till then, all products will be sourced from the Korea facility.
